						<summary>

						<p>On the west wall, central shrine, Vaidyanātha temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Year 6: 977 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>It records that Tirukkuṉṟam-uḍaiyān Kāman Tāyan of Vātti in Iḍaiyāṟu, donated 90 sheep for burning a perpetual lamp with an <hi rend="italic">uḻakku</hi> of ghee daily to the god Tirumaḻavāḍi Mahādēva. He also donated a stud-ram and a floor-based lamp <hi rend="italic">(nilai-viḷakku).</hi></p>						

						<p>Published in <hi rend="italic">S.I.I.,</hi> Vol. XIX No. 167.</p>						

						</summary>
